gomodel:SYNGO_193  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Rab10 was detected by mass spectrometry on highly purified synaptic vesicles. This was further validated using anti-Rab10 antibody by immunoblotting and by staining of GFP-Rab10 with synaptophysin in transiently transfected hippocampal neurons. The presence of Rab10 in synaptic vesicles was separately identified in another study (Takamori et al., 2006; PMID 17110340) by mass spectrometry.. Experimental description: Legend to Figure 2 \"Enrichment profiles of Rab GTPases on purified SVs isolated from rat brain homogenates, determined by quantitative immunoblotting.\"\n\n20/2/2017 Pim:\nSpecies of Rab10 OE construct used in Fig.3 is not stated in the M&M. Table 1 and Fig.2 are sufficient to claim the selected term, however, and species is set to Rat." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0098993 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
